<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 01-09-04 - Repair Procedures for New 9900 Hoods</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi010904" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>01-09-04</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>December, 2001</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>FRONT END SHEET METAL</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Repair Procedures for New 9900 Hoods</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9900</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Implementation of a new hood material for 9900 models began in February 2001 and was fully
                    in-effect by May 9, 2001. The new hoods are made using high impact Metton plastic in lieu of FRP
                    (fiberglass reinforced plastic). The high impact Metton material no longer requires the addition of
                    urethane sheeting or a rubberized undercoating to protect the fenders from stone impacts and spider
                    cracking. The new hoods can be identified by the name Paramount Mfg. or 21st Century Mfg. on a plate
                    attached to the rear of the hood.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Repairs</title>
            <svcprocinfo>
                <para>Cracks no more than 4" in length, and scratches, nicks and gouges in Metton components can be
                    repaired using the following processes. Repairs should be performed at room temperature.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The Fusor repair products mentioned in this letter are available Direct Ship - see Parts
                            letter G-19-4577-A dated May 15, 2001.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>To avoid personal injury, use safety goggles, dust mask and gloves.</para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </svcprocinfo>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Repairing the underside of cracks no more than 4" in length:</title>
                <table id="t0109041">
                    <title>Repairing the underside of cracks no more than 4" in length:</title>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
                        <colspec colname="col1" align="center" colwidth="0.33*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.45*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.24*"/>
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>Step</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                    <para>Procedure</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                                    <para>Tools and Parts Required</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>1.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Using a shop towel, clean the repair area with Fusor #703 adhesion prep
                                        cleaner and allow to air dry.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Fusor #703 adhesion prep cleaner (water based), clean shop towel</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>2.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Scuff area with a DA (Dual Action) sander using 80 grit sandpaper. Blow off
                                        with dry compressed air and then wipe clean with a dry shop towel.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>DA sander, 80 grit sandpaper, clean dry shop towel</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>3.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Prepare a backing patch of Fusor #702 fiberglass cloth cut to extend 1" in all
                                        directions from the crack.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Fusor #702 fiberglass cloth</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>4.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Apply a medium thickness film of Fusor T10 plastic structural repair adhesive
                                        to extend approximately 1&#189;" in all directions from the crack using a Fusor
                                        #301 manual dispenser and clean disposable plastic spreader.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Fusor T10 plastic structural repair adhesive, Fusor #301 manual dispenser,
                                        clean disposable plastic spreader.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>5.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Lay in the pre-cut backing patch of fiberglass cloth.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para></para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>6.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Apply another thin film of Fusor T10 plastic structural repair adhesive using
                                        clean disposable plastic spreader, working the adhesive into the fiberglass and
                                        feathering the edges of the entire repair area.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Fusor T10 plastic structural repair adhesive, Fusor #301 manual dispenser,
                                        clean disposable plastic spreader.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>7.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Heat the repair area with a heat gun or heat lamp to 140&#176; F for 10
                                        minutes or until hard. Do not overheat.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Heat gun or heat lamp</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Repairing the cosmetic side of cracks no more than 4" in length:</title>
                <table id="t0109042">
                    <title>Repairing the cosmetic side of cracks no more than 4" in length:</title>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
                        <colspec colname="col1" align="center" colwidth="0.33*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.46*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.23*"/>
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>Step</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                    <para>Procedure</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                                    <para>Tools and Parts Required</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>1.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Using a shop towel, clean the repair area with Fusor #703 adhesion prep
                                        cleaner and allow to air dry.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Fusor #703 adhesion prep cleaner (water based), clean shop towel</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>2.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Dish out the cracked area with a DA (Dual Action) sander using 80 grit
                                        sandpaper or an angle grinder using 36 grit sandpaper. Extend taper to bottom of
                                        damage. Feather all edges. Do not allow sander to heat surface of panel to
                                        melting point.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>DA (Dual Action) sander, 80 grit sandpaper, angle grinder, 36 grit sandpaper
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>3.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Follow-up by hand block sanding all areas to be refinished with 80 grit
                                        sandpaper.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>80 grit sandpaper, sanding block</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>4.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Blow off with dry compressed air and then wipe clean with a dry shop towel.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Clean, dry shop towel</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>5.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Apply Fusor T10 plastic structural repair adhesive (slow/heat set) or T9
                                        finishing adhesive (fast set) to fill the repair area using a plastic spreader
                                        and spread smooth.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Fusor T10 plastic structural repair adhesive (slow/heat set) and Fusor #301
                                        manual dispenser OR T9 finishing adhesive (fast set - no dispenser or mixer
                                        needed), clean disposable plastic spreader.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>6.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>If using Fusor T9, and cure at room temperature for 15 minutes before
                                        sanding.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para></para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>7.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>If using Fusor T10, cure with heat gun or heat lamp at 140&#176; F for 10
                                        minutes or until hard before sanding. Do not overheat.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Heat gun or heat lamp</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>8.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Sand affected area with a DA (Dual Action) sander using 80 grit sandpaper
                                        followed by 180/220 grit sandpaper. Finish block sand by hand.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>DA (Dual Action) sander, 80 grit sandpaper, 180/220 grit sandpaper, sanding
                                        block
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>9.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Let stand for 1 hour, then prime and paint per the paint manufacturer&#x2019;s
                                        specifications.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para></para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Repairing cosmetic surface scratches, nicks and gouges</title>
                <table id="t0109043">
                    <title>Repairing cosmetic surface scratches, nicks and gouges</title>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
                        <colspec colname="col1" align="center" colwidth="0.33*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.42*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.26*"/>
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>Step</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                    <para>Procedure</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                                    <para>Tools and Parts Required</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>1.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Using a shop towel, clean the repair area with Fusor #703 adhesion prep
                                        cleaner and allow to air dry.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Fusor #703 adhesion prep cleaner (water based), clean shop towel</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>2.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Dish out the cracked area with a DA (Dual Action) sander using 80 grit
                                        sandpaper or an angle grinder using 36 grit sandpaper. Extend taper to bottom of
                                        damage. Feather all edges. Do not allow sander to heat surface of panel to
                                        melting point
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>DA (Dual Action) sander, 80 grit sandpaper, angle grinder, 36 grit sandpaper
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>3.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Follow-up by hand block sanding all areas to be refinished with 80 grit
                                        sandpaper.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>80 grit sandpaper, sanding block</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>4.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Blow off with dry compressed air and then wipe clean with a dry shop towel.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Clean, dry shop towel</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>5.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Dispense a quantity of Fusor T9 finishing adhesive (fast set) onto a mixing
                                        board and then quickly apply to fill the repair area using a plastic spreader
                                        and spread smooth.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Fusor T9 finishing adhesive (fast set), mixing board, clean disposable plastic
                                        spreader
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>6.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Let cure at room temperature for 15 minutes before sanding.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para></para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>7.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Sand affected area with a DA (Dual Action) sander using 80 grit sandpaper
                                        followed by 180/220 grit sandpaper. Finish block sand by hand.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>DA (Dual Action) sander, 80 grit sandpaper, 180/220 grit sandpaper, sanding
                                        block
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center" colname="col1">
                                    <para>8.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <para>Let stand for 1 hour, then prime and paint per the paint manufacturer&#x2019;s
                                        specifications.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para></para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Further information on Fusor products can be found on their web site: www.fusor.com</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </svcsubproc>
        </svcproc>
